### 4. Main Orchestrator

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///d:/just%20learning/ghostnet/main.py)

- Initialize `BreadcrumbAgent` alongside other agents
- Each session now creates a `SessionDatabase(session_id)` stored in `active_sessions[session_id]["session_db"]`
- All [log_command](file:///d:/just%20learning/ghostnet/state_manager/database.py#99-111), [log_threat_event](file:///d:/just%20learning/ghostnet/state_manager/database.py#112-124) calls use `session_db` (not the main db)
- After each command, spawn background thread:
  ```python
  threading.Thread(target=self._breadcrumb_pipeline,
                   args=(command, session_id), daemon=True).start()
  ```
- `_breadcrumb_pipeline`:
  1. `intent, confidence = breadcrumb_agent.detect_intent(command, history)`
  2. `session_db.log_intent(intent, confidence, command)`
  3. If `breadcrumb_agent.should_plant(session_id)`:
     - `filename, content = breadcrumb_agent.generate_breadcrumb(intent, cwd_path)`
     - Inject [FSNode](file:///d:/just%20learning/ghostnet/state_manager/file_system.py#17-87) into session filesystem at current directory
     - `session_db.register_canary(cwd + "/" + filename, intent)`
- `_on_canary_triggered(session_id, canary_info)`:
  - `session_db.log_threat_event("canary_accessed", "critical", canary_info)`
  - Logs: `⚠️ CRITICAL: Attacker accessed canary '{filepath}' — Intent: {intent}`

